body:
You guys are never content.
Ever.

When Mages are in an okay position &quot;Mages are so weak! Riot needs to get their shit together or fix this or I&#039;m quitting League!&quot;
When mages are buffed &quot;Mages are way too strong. I can&#039;t believe that Riot buffed them so much. Riot needs to get their shit together or I&#039;m quitting League!&quot;

When assassins are strong &quot;Oh my god, Riot I get deleted in .4 seconds, it&#039;s so unfair and there&#039;s no counterplay! Gut them and leave them to rot, I don&#039;t even care.&quot;
When said assassins get nerfed &quot;Riot, you went way too hard on these poor fellows. I can&#039;t even play them anymore they&#039;re so bad&quot;

I get that there are meta shifts and some champion will always be fotm, that&#039;s kinda the point of fotm. But oh my god, you people need to make up your minds.
Overall, the gameplay boards don&#039;t know how to leave shit alone. If a champion does well in their lane when played correctly, then that champion is FINE. If another champion is stronger for doing less work, that&#039;s a problem with that champion. I hope I&#039;m not the only one that wants Riot to nerf instead of buff everyone.

When I think of this, I remember S5 when Riot was nerfing everyone, and people were up in arms. They said they would much rather have champions buffed than nerfed. Now in S6, everyone is complaining about too much damage.

It just feels like Gameplay wants to find something to complain about and circlejerk about. Perhaps that&#039;s the natural way of the boards, but can we all just chill out a little bit, take a step back, and assess how things REALLY are and carefully think about our balance ideas before we go spewing them onto half the Hot page.
